
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Localization;
@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer

<style>
    p {
        font-size: 18px;
    }

    .masthead {
        height: 100vh;
        min-height: 200px;
        max-height: 350px;
        background-image: url('/img/privacy-policy.jpg');
        background-size: cover;
        background-position: center;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
    }

        .masthead::before {
            content: "";
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            position: absolute;
            top: 129px;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 350px;
        }
</style>

<header class="masthead">
    <div class="container h-100">
        <div class="row h-100 align-items-center">
            <div class="col-12 text-center">
                <h1 class="fw-light">@Localizer["PrivacyPolicyHeading"]</h1>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</header>

<div class="container px-5">

    @Localizer["FirstPartWithouLink"]
@*
    <p class="mb-3 mt-5">
        If you visit the city-media.nl website, your privacy-sensitive data or personal data may be processed.
        City Media considers your privacy to be of great importance.
        To guarantee your privacy as best as possible, we apply a number of core values.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">To inform.</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">We want to inform you as well as possible about how and why we process personal data. We do this via this privacy and cookie statement.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">Limit collection.</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">We pay close attention to ensuring that our collection of personal data is limited to what is necessary for the proper functioning of the website and the services you request.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">To secure.</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">We take appropriate security measures to protect your personal data and also require this from parties that process personal data on our behalf.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">Permission.</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">We request explicit consent to process your personal data in cases where your consent is required by law.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">Rights of data subjects.</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">We respect your right to view, correct or delete the personal data we process about you and any other rights you have under applicable privacy legislation. In this privacy and cookie statement you can read how we put these core values ​​into practice and respect and protect your right to privacy.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">The use of personal data.</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">When using our website, you may leave certain information with us. This can also be personal data. We only collect, store and use personal data that you provide directly (for example via the contact form on the website) or for which it is clear that it is provided to us for processing.</p>
    <p class="mb-3">We will not use your personal data for purposes other than those for which we obtained it, unless you have given your prior permission or we are allowed or required to do so by law.</p>
    <p class="mb-3">Depending on which functionalities you use via the website, we may process the following personal data from you:</p>

    <ul class="text-white ml-4">
        <li>name and address details;</li>
        <li>phone number;</li>
        <li>billing address;</li>
        <li>e-mail address;</li>
        <li>payment details;</li>
        <li>sex;</li>
        <li>IP address.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-5">Your personal data will be used by us for the purposes below (and for purposes closely related to them):</h2>
    
    <ul class="text-white ml-4 mt-3">
        <li>creating your account;</li>
        <li>controlling access to your account;</li>
        <li>handling your orders;</li>
        <li>invoicing the services purchased;</li>
        <li>sending newsletters;</li>
        <li>improving and evaluating our website and services;</li>
        <li>answering and handling questions you ask;</li>
        <li>offering targeted advertisements via search engines.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-5">Contact forms and emails</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">If you have any questions about City Media or the services we offer, please contact us. You can contact us via the contact form on our website and by e-mail. Please see our contact page for current contact details.</p>
    
    <p class="mb-3">If you fill in the contact form on the contact page, or if you send us an e-mail, the data you send us will be kept for as long as the nature of the form or the content of your e-mail requires it for a complete response and handling thereof.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">Cookies</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">Cookies are used on our website. A cookie is a small file that is sent with the pages of our website and stored in the memory of your device. The information stored in a cookie can be transferred to our own secure server or that of a third party.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">We distinguish three types of cookies:</h2>
    <h2 class="mt-5">Functional cookies</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">These cookies ensure the proper functioning of our website. In addition, they ensure that you can use the website more easily by, for example, remembering your personal settings.</p>
*@

